# Remember to never publicly share your keystore.
# See https://flutter.dev/to/reference-keystore
key.properties
**/*.keystore
**/*.jks
# …except Séance's committed release keystore. It is deliberately public: the
# app is sideloaded (no Play Store), so the key carries debug-grade trust by
# design — committing it is what gives every build (local or CI) the SAME
# signing identity, so a downloaded release APK upgrades an installed one
# instead of demanding an uninstall (which would wipe the app's local data).
!app/ci-release.jks
